Willis Towers Watson PLC

The Willis Building 51 Lime Street
London  EC3M7DQ United Kingdom
Phone: +44 20 ____ ____
Fax: +44 20 ____ ____
https://www.willistowerswatson.com





15
Managers




221
IT employees




$134.8MEST.
IT Budget




Willis Tower Watson, based in the UK, provides insurance brokerage, reinsurance, and risk management consulting services worldwide. It has major clients in the aerospace, construction, energy, and marine industries.

Willis Group merged with Tower Watson in January, 2016, to form Willis… MoreWillis Tower Watson, based in the UK, provides insurance brokerage, reinsurance, and risk management consulting services worldwide. It has major clients in the aerospace, construction, energy, and marine industries.

Willis Group merged with Tower Watson in January, 2016, to form Willis Tower Watson.
December 2015 Jordan 1/2016
Willis Group Holdings plc (NYSE: WSH) will replace Fossil Group Inc. (NASD:FOSL) in the S&P 500

Willis Group is merging with Towers Watson in a deal expected to be completed on or about that date pending final conditions. Post… MoreDecember 2015 Jordan 1/2016
Willis Group Holdings plc (NYSE: WSH) will replace Fossil Group Inc. (NASD:FOSL) in the S&P 500

Willis Group is merging with Towers Watson in a deal expected to be completed on or about that date pending final conditions. Post merger, Willis Group Holdings will change its name to Willis Towers Watson plc and trade under the ticker symbol "WLTW". 

• Maintains a $1M-$5M help desk management contract with ServiceNow.
• Maintains a $1M-$5M legacy application support contract with KForce.
• Maintains a $250,000-$1M disaster recovery contract with HP.
• The organization expects its unstructured storage to grow 20-49% in the next 12 months.
• The organization's total data storage volume under management is more than 5 Petabytes.
• The organization's weekly backup is greater than 100TB. IT Priorities:
•The company is developing custom enterprise and testing applications.

IT Structure
•While Willis's CIO leads the IT group from New York, most of the company's IT management is spread across the company's US and UK locations.

IT Intelligence Snippets

2013
•The company operates a global data center in Nashville and a backup data center in Ipswitch.
•Willis utilizes a consolidated IT infrastructure using Riverbed Steelhead appliances.

2012
•The company standardized its storage using EMC VNX unified storage, VMWare, and Cisco UCS.





